  "texts": [
    "This finding prompts a critical inquiry: Do we want LLMs to reflect these social stereotypes?",
    "The dichotomy lies in the potential dual role of LLMs -acting both descriptively as mirrors reflecting societal biases and normatively as influential contributors to the perpetuation of these biases.",
    "Emotions serve as heuristics to interpret a given situation, and we learn to interpret this heuristic given societal cues during our upbringing.",
    "We might thus be tempted to justify models' varying predictions, given that people of different genders might interpret the same event differently.",
    "However, while we may experience emotions differently due to factors such as gender, models do not only reflect but severely amplify this disparity: in our results, models overwhelmingly predict SADNESS for women and ANGER for men, even when the annotators themselves labeled different emotions."
  ],
